  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison gives Oliver Johnson permission to make changes to his article for the Independent. The Rev. George Porter asked Garrison for loan of money upon finding himself &quot;temporarily straitened on his arrival in New York.&quot; Garrison thinks he may not get a dollar back &quot;not for lack of honesty of purpose, but because it may prove a case of &apos;chronic poverty.&apos;&quot; Several weeks ago Garrison loaned twenty dollars to Peter Sinclair, a Scottish temperance leader now interested in European immigration to the United States. Garrison has experienced many instances of not having his money returned. Garrison&apos;s letter to Susan B. Anthony was a private one, &quot;concerning that nondescript Train.&quot; Mrs. Stanton violated that privacy by printing it.</subfield>
